###  https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/PartialPressure
hto:PartialPressure rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000145 ;
                    dc:source "DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 eq.3 (p_NH3, p_H2 in K_N formula)" ;
                    rdfs:isDefinedBy hto: ;
                    rdfs:label "partial pressure"@en ;
                    skos:definition " Paramenter describing the intended pressure inside a chamber targeted in a factor relative to one bar (using a vakuum cooling or an atmosphere flow). The complement to vacuum-heating as it allows for active vacuum pump during atmosphere flow. Should be set to zero, if vacuum-heating is true. "@en ,
                                    "Describing the intended pressure inside a chamber targeted in a factor relative to one bar (using a vakuum cooling or an atmosphere flow)."@en ,
                                    "Parameter describing the amount of a specific gas species in a mixture, could be mbar "@en ,
                                    "The complement to vacuum-heating as it allows for active vacuum pump during atmosphere flow. Should be set to zero, if vacuum-heating is true."@en ,
                                    "nominal pressure of a specific atmosphere component thermochemical steps "@en ,
                                    "nominal pressure of thermochemical heat treatment pressure during thermochemical steps "@en ;
                    skos:editorialNote "DIN audit (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 has no §3 entry for partial pressure; this is upstream physical-chemistry vocabulary, not DIN-terminology-native. Operational usage in DIN 17022-4 §7.3 (p_NH3, p_H2 in K_N formula) is the only DIN anchor."@en .


